The founder and Publisher of LEADERSHIP Newspapers Group which publishes LEADERSHIP, A Yau and National Economy, Mr. Sam Nda Isaiah has said that fake news remains one of the major existential threats for legacy media in Nigeria. The Publisher who was speaking on NTA weekend file said the advancement of the internet and proliferation of social media platforms has made it easy for purveyors of fake news to have a field day. Mr. Nda Isaiah during the conversation monitored by LEADERSHIP In Bauchi said only professionally driven journalism will stand the taste of time in the era of fake news and sensational reportage. “Sometimes governors called me, that they have seen so and so, and I used to ask them; have you seen it on any traditional media?. The publisher said the legacy media remains an alternative hub where people verify the authenticity of stories that may appear sensational or fake on social media platforms. Mr. Nda Isaiah said it is in the enlightened self interest of media owners to mentor decent and innovative journalists to take over the media space. He said only robust journalism anchored on the principle of social responsibility could save Nigeria’s fragile democracy. The publisher argued that the press occupies a vital space “as the fourth estate of the realm” in Nigeria’s sojourn to good and responsive governance that ought to address the needs of Nigerians. He called on the media to continue to play its roles by holding public officials accountable, insisting that it was the only yardstick to canvass for good governance and sustain the current democratic legacies in Nigeria.